cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.SE 

This paper discusses a security and privacy issue related to mobile devices, specifically the leakage of information through the magnetometer sensor. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the impact on end-users' privacy, which suggests a possible fit for cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The paper also mentions the evaluation of 80 models of modern smartphones and tablets, which suggests a possible fit for cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the use of sensor data, which suggests a possible fit for cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses possible countermeasures, which suggests a possible fit for cs.SE (Software Engineering).
